Kisumu Central ODM leaders want the party national elections board to issue a direct ticket to a suitable candidate.The elections board directed a repeat nomination for the constituency yesterday.The officials on Monday said they received numerous complaints from voters about the timing and preparedness.A court ordered a repeat election after former TNA secretary general Onyango Oloo appealed against the nomination of the incumbent, Ken Obura.The six ward chairmen said time constraint may lead to more legal battles and ODM missing out of the IEBC candidates&rsquo; roll.Led by Kondele ward ODM chairman George Anayo, they said most of the polling stations were schools, where learning has resumed. Anayo said they will support the board&rsquo;s choice.